Well, he-he made them
from bedsheets.

02:49.961 --> 02:53.882
A guard cut him free
and tried to revive him.

02:53.965 --> 02:57.594
-And the guard can't tell us?
-He's being prosecuted.

03:02.515 --> 03:05.101
LIZ:
Can we... can we get
a photo of that?

03:05.184 --> 03:06.978
-GUARD: Sure.
-NIKO: They're lying!

03:08.521 --> 03:10.607
-They're all lying.
-Shut up.

03:10.690 --> 03:12.150
Back away.

03:12.233 --> 03:15.653
-How many prisoners per cell?
-WILBUR: Two...

03:15.737 --> 03:17.947
in the Special Housing Unit.

03:18.031 --> 03:20.450
But no one in that cell?

03:20.533 --> 03:21.367
WILBUR:
Correct.

03:21.451 --> 03:24.162
And when was
the second prisoner removed?

03:24.245 --> 03:25.914
-The day before.
-Why?

03:25.997 --> 03:27.665
He was released.

03:27.749 --> 03:30.960
(chuckles) This prison
is massively overcrowded?

03:31.044 --> 03:34.380
-Mm.
-And no one was put
in that cell?

03:35.381 --> 03:37.133
So he was on suicide watch,

03:37.216 --> 03:39.677
but he was allowed to be
in that cell by himself?

03:39.761 --> 03:41.763
He was taken off watch
a week later.

03:43.556 --> 03:46.768
And that video camera, that's
the one that wasn't working?

03:46.851 --> 03:48.853
-Yes.
-And we don't know why?

03:50.229 --> 03:52.148
But there was
another video camera?

03:52.231 --> 03:53.650
Yes.

03:56.027 --> 03:57.820
LIZ:
But you don't have the footage

03:57.904 --> 03:59.614
-from this one?
-No.

03:59.697 --> 04:03.034
But Bill Barr has reviewed it,
and he saw nothing unusual.

04:03.117 --> 04:05.745
No one entering the SHU
or exiting.

04:05.828 --> 04:07.956
-The attorney general saw this?
-Yes.

04:08.039 --> 04:09.791
But we can't see it?

04:09.874 --> 04:12.377
It wasn't made available
to my department.

04:12.460 --> 04:15.129
You're the U.S. attorney, and it
wasn't made available to you?

04:15.213 --> 04:16.714
Yes.

04:16.798 --> 04:21.344
Look, Liz, that's why
I need you to review this.

04:24.430 --> 04:27.809
We thought that the media
attention would die down,

04:27.892 --> 04:31.980
but it's been nine months,
and the reporters keep calling

04:32.063 --> 04:34.691
and asking,
"Did he kill himself,

04:34.774 --> 04:37.026
or was Jeffrey Epstein
murdered?"

04:37.110 --> 04:39.195
So, why me?

04:39.278 --> 04:40.863
-We're objective.
-WILBUR: That's right.

04:40.947 --> 04:43.533
I need my own Warren Commission.

04:43.616 --> 04:47.996
This is a printout
of Epstein's little black book.

04:48.079 --> 04:50.373
It has every name
of every lawyer

04:50.456 --> 04:52.542
worth his salt in New York.

04:52.625 --> 04:55.003
You worked for me in Chicago.

04:55.086 --> 04:57.171
-You pushed me out in Chicago.
-Yes, but I remember

04:57.255 --> 04:59.549
you came to me five years ago
and you told me,

04:59.632 --> 05:01.551
"We should arrest
Jeffrey Epstein."

05:01.634 --> 05:04.929
You wanted to investigate
his sexual transporting

05:05.013 --> 05:06.681
of underage girls.

05:06.764 --> 05:08.266
You were ahead of all of us.

05:08.349 --> 05:12.061
You kept saying,
"We need to protect the girls,"

05:12.145 --> 05:14.897
and I said,
"No, he's too connected."

05:14.981 --> 05:17.942
Well, here's our chance
to correct that.

05:18.026 --> 05:21.571
-Yeah, well, it's a little late.
-You do a good job here, Liz,

05:21.654 --> 05:23.948
I can imply but not promise

05:24.032 --> 05:26.451
that there could be other work
for your firm.

05:26.534 --> 05:27.994
A lot of work.

05:31.956 --> 05:34.250
Epstein died in this cell.

05:34.334 --> 05:37.545
Did he commit suicide,
or was he murdered?

05:37.628 --> 05:40.256
You have a budget of $400,000,

05:40.339 --> 05:44.135
and 133,000 pages of evidence.

05:44.218 --> 05:46.721
And if I decide
that he was murdered?

05:46.804 --> 05:48.806
-I won't censor you.
-Even if I find out

05:48.890 --> 05:50.808
that it was done
by powerful people?

05:50.892 --> 05:53.269
Follow the evidence
wherever it takes you.

05:53.352 --> 05:55.438
I need outside-the-box thinking.

05:55.521 --> 05:57.273
-How long do I have?
-Two weeks.

05:57.356 --> 05:59.650
-(sighs)
-Brief me in a week,
I'll get you more time.

05:59.734 --> 06:02.278
But I need something.

06:02.361 --> 06:05.198
Something 60 Minutes
doesn't have.

06:06.365 --> 06:08.159
All right, you...

06:08.242 --> 06:09.994
You told me that I could
interview somebody

06:10.078 --> 06:11.245
who knew Epstein in prison?

06:11.329 --> 06:12.830
Yes. This way.

06:12.914 --> 06:14.749
No, no, no, no. I want him.

06:14.832 --> 06:16.834
GUARD:
No. That's Niko.

06:16.918 --> 06:19.462
-He's a liar.
-Yeah, it's better if you
talk to someone else.

06:19.545 --> 06:21.089
Was Niko there that night?

06:22.799 --> 06:25.426
Then-then I want to talk to him.

06:25.510 --> 06:27.845
(muffled): He used to stand
just inside that door.

06:27.929 --> 06:29.472
We talked a lot.

06:29.555 --> 06:31.933
He gave me investment advice
about index funds

06:32.016 --> 06:33.559
that I'm definitely
going to follow.

06:33.643 --> 06:36.270
Do you remember anything
about the night that he died?

06:38.231 --> 06:40.399
He was kind of chatty
that night, said he, uh,

06:40.483 --> 06:43.653
had doubts about the Jets'
starting quarterback.

06:43.736 --> 06:46.197
And then he said
something weird.

06:47.865 --> 06:49.992
He said, right before
he was arrested, on his jet,

06:50.076 --> 06:52.370
he took care of
the most important thing.

06:53.412 --> 06:55.331
What was that?

06:56.415 --> 06:58.334
I have no idea.

07:06.134 --> 07:07.844
Any idea what this is about?

07:07.927 --> 07:09.512
Nope.

07:09.595 --> 07:12.223
But an unscheduled
midweek meeting?

07:12.306 --> 07:14.142
(chuckles):
Never good.

07:14.225 --> 07:15.643
The coffee's better up here,
though, huh?

07:15.726 --> 07:17.687
-Mm.
-(laughs)

07:17.770 --> 07:20.982
Ah, good morning. Thank you
for starting your day with me.

07:21.065 --> 07:23.192
I will make this quick.

07:23.276 --> 07:26.362
You are the heads of all
of our major departments,

07:26.445 --> 07:29.407
and you're doing an amazing job.

07:29.490 --> 07:31.284
-(scattered applause)
-That... Yes.

07:31.367 --> 07:33.536
Yes. Applause. Indeed, indeed.

07:33.619 --> 07:35.872
Well-deserved. Worth it.

07:37.248 --> 07:38.833
I have very good news
for everyone.

07:38.916 --> 07:40.209
-Here it comes.
-One of the reasons

07:40.293 --> 07:42.670
for these mergers is the great

07:42.753 --> 07:44.881
opportunity for synergy.

07:44.964 --> 07:47.383
It gives us the-the chance
to hone our operations,

07:47.466 --> 07:51.762
to create greater communication,
to maximize profits.

07:51.846 --> 07:54.223
I mean, y-you carefully sand
a piece of wood

07:54.307 --> 07:56.058
in order to reduce
the chance of slivers.

07:56.142 --> 07:57.894
Now, as department heads,

07:57.977 --> 08:00.897
I want you to take a look at
your lawyers and associates,

08:00.980 --> 08:04.692
and then I want you to come
back to me with suggestions

08:04.775 --> 08:07.195
for reductions of 20%.

08:07.278 --> 08:10.406
We've made copies
of your personnel lists.

08:10.489 --> 08:12.074
Just go through them.

08:12.158 --> 08:13.951
Put an "X" next to

08:14.035 --> 08:16.913
whoever you think
we might be able to reduce.

08:16.996 --> 08:20.416
We will handle notification,
severance packages and the like.

08:20.499 --> 08:23.044
Now, look, there are
exciting days ahead.

08:23.127 --> 08:24.754
Let us remember
the words of the master:

08:24.837 --> 08:27.423
"Only when we are soft
and pliable

08:27.506 --> 08:30.593
can we be hard and strong."

08:32.637 --> 08:34.138
You're dictating
our staffing levels.

08:34.222 --> 08:35.765
I don't consider it dictating.

08:35.848 --> 08:37.767
-What do you consider it?
-Stewardship.

08:37.850 --> 08:41.479
Which, by the way, significantly
increases all our incomes.

08:41.562 --> 08:43.439
Except for the people
who are fired.

08:43.522 --> 08:45.900
You can't force us to lay off
20% of our employees.

08:45.983 --> 08:48.653
-How do you figure?
-Because we agreed
that for the first year,

08:48.736 --> 08:51.197
we would be allowed
to supervise our own shop.

08:51.280 --> 08:53.950
-It's in our contract.
-And you are.

08:54.033 --> 08:56.619
I'm not telling you
who to let go.

08:56.702 --> 08:58.454
Just put an "X" by their name.

08:58.538 --> 09:00.748
We'll take care
of the rest of it.

09:00.831 --> 09:02.541
♪ ♪

09:09.507 --> 09:11.384
There are so many files
to go through here.

09:11.467 --> 09:12.927
This is just
the first truckload.

09:13.010 --> 09:13.970
We're gonna be at this
for weeks.

09:14.053 --> 09:16.806
We're gonna need a system
to get this organized.

09:16.889 --> 09:18.266
Who wrote all these reports?

09:18.349 --> 09:19.976
Oh, there it is. All right.

09:20.059 --> 09:22.270
Okay, let's put the... let's put
the medical evidence here,

09:22.353 --> 09:23.854
we'll put the correspondence
here, and let's put

09:23.938 --> 09:25.815
the interviews
with the prison officials here.

09:25.898 --> 09:27.191
I've never worked on
a case this famous before.

09:27.275 --> 09:29.318
-I know, right?
-This is criminal charges

09:29.402 --> 09:31.487
-and victims' accounts?
-LIZ: Okay, why don't you get

09:31.570 --> 09:33.614
a team of three
and go through all of that?

09:33.698 --> 09:35.283
Okay, look, find any evidence

09:35.366 --> 09:38.160
that argues for murder
or suicide, you put it here.

09:38.244 --> 09:40.288
Murder. He was killed
by the Trumps.

09:40.371 --> 09:42.081
-KEVIN: Oh, come on.
-You blame everything
on the Trumps.

09:42.164 --> 09:45.001
Nobody in Trumpland is organized
enough to pull this off.

09:45.084 --> 09:47.003
-KEVIN: Why not the Clintons?
-MICAH: You sound like
right-wing talk radio.

09:47.086 --> 09:48.170
Bill was on
the Lolita Express, too.

09:48.254 --> 09:49.338
LIZ:
Hey! Wait, no.

09:49.422 --> 09:52.008
No. No conspiracy theories,

09:52.091 --> 09:53.843
no... no insane charges.

09:53.926 --> 09:56.679
Everything we do, we need
evidence, so let's start here.

09:56.762 --> 10:00.349
Epstein was a middle-aged
white man.

10:00.433 --> 10:02.685
That is the demographic
most likely to die by suicide.

10:02.768 --> 10:05.521
It says here suicide rate
in pretrial jails

10:05.604 --> 10:07.565
is three times higher
than in other prisons.

10:07.648 --> 10:10.359
Yes, but the last suicide
in that jail was 21 years ago.

10:10.443 --> 10:12.028
It was unusual.

10:12.111 --> 10:13.529
LIZ:
Yeah, but Epstein knew
that he was going

10:13.612 --> 10:15.364
to prison for the rest
of his life.

10:15.448 --> 10:17.158
So let's not rule out
the simplest explanation.

10:17.241 --> 10:18.617
ROSALYN:
Actually, there are
two autopsy reports.

10:18.701 --> 10:20.328
One by a private examiner.

10:20.411 --> 10:22.038
-Paid for by the family?
-So?

10:22.121 --> 10:24.373
Maybe he's just telling them
what they want to hear.

10:24.457 --> 10:26.000
He thinks that
Epstein's injuries

10:26.083 --> 10:27.543
are more consistent
with homicide.

10:27.626 --> 10:29.045
Broken blood vessels
in the eyes,

10:29.128 --> 10:30.629
broken hyoid bone
and cartilage.

10:30.713 --> 10:32.673
But the official report
says that injuries like that

10:32.757 --> 10:34.550
-are not unusual in hanging.
-MICAH: They got a reason

10:34.633 --> 10:36.218
-to protect their own asses.
-Key words there
are "official report."

10:36.302 --> 10:38.220
Look, why is it so hard
to believe that a professional,

10:38.304 --> 10:41.015
well-respected medical examiner
could be telling the truth?

10:41.098 --> 10:43.726
Look, Epstein ties his bedsheets
into a noose, right?

10:43.809 --> 10:45.353
Then he tied it around his neck.

10:45.436 --> 10:49.065
It's not gonna be
a clean, sharp cut like this.

10:49.148 --> 10:52.735
His weight is gonna
push the noose up like that.

10:52.818 --> 10:55.488
-Uh, actually, I feel like...
-(overlapping chatter)

10:55.571 --> 10:57.406
LIZ:
Guys.

10:58.657 --> 11:00.034
(sighs)

11:02.328 --> 11:04.997
(indistinct chatter)

11:11.170 --> 11:12.296
MARISSA:
Okay, whoa, whoa, whoa, wait.

11:12.380 --> 11:13.798
Wait, wait. You guys.

11:13.881 --> 11:15.424
He could've... he could've
paid someone else

11:15.508 --> 11:16.759
-to break his neck.
-Or someone had him killed.

11:16.842 --> 11:18.761
-Oh, back to Trump again.
-Well, of course
it goes back to Trump.

11:18.844 --> 11:19.762
LEAH:
If the tiny glove fits...

11:19.845 --> 11:22.098
All right, l-let's...
let's stay on track.

11:22.181 --> 11:23.974
Liz, Liz, uh, we need to talk.

11:24.058 --> 11:26.268
Oh. All right. Just, uh,
give me... give me one minute.

11:26.352 --> 11:27.978
We start with the obvious.

11:28.062 --> 11:29.438
But suicide isn't the obvious.

11:29.522 --> 11:31.232
That's just
the official version.

11:31.315 --> 11:33.109
This is everything
that had to go wrong

11:33.192 --> 11:34.777
for Epstein to commit suicide.

11:34.860 --> 11:36.987
Start with the suicide attempt
a few weeks earlier.

11:37.071 --> 11:39.990
This was July 23, right after
he'd been denied bail.

11:40.074 --> 11:41.909
They found him unconscious
in his cell.

11:41.992 --> 11:44.537
(voice fading): There was video
of this suicide attempt...

11:51.502 --> 11:53.504
(voice muted)

11:55.381 --> 11:57.133
Isn't that the video
of his actual suicide?

11:57.216 --> 11:58.968
JAY:
No, this was a week earlier.

11:59.051 --> 12:00.136
It's a different missing video.

12:00.219 --> 12:02.596
They put him on suicide watch
for less than a week.

12:02.680 --> 12:04.473
(voice fading): Then Epstein was
taken off suicide watch

12:04.557 --> 12:06.475
and placed...

12:06.559 --> 12:08.102
(voice muted)

12:08.185 --> 12:09.520
KEVIN:
So, everyone gets a cellmate

12:09.603 --> 12:10.896
except for the suicidal man?

12:10.980 --> 12:12.022
LUCCA:
It's the worst jail in America.

12:12.106 --> 12:13.149
What do you expect?

12:13.232 --> 12:14.650
LEAH:
Reportedly understaffed

12:14.733 --> 12:17.653
as a result of a hiring freeze
imposed by who?

12:17.736 --> 12:19.321
-The Trump administration.
-MICAH: Why am I not surprised?

12:19.405 --> 12:21.323
-Why am I not surprised?
-ROSALYN: The second M.E. said

12:21.407 --> 12:22.658
that the noose found
in the autopsy report

12:22.741 --> 12:24.118
did not match the wounds
on his neck.

12:24.201 --> 12:25.453
That is consistent
with homicide.

12:25.536 --> 12:26.787
Who cares about
the autopsy report?

12:26.871 --> 12:29.373
(overlapping chatter)

12:37.256 --> 12:39.008
-Um, uh...
-Hey, guys.

12:39.091 --> 12:41.927
There is another way
to look at this.

12:43.095 --> 12:45.014
Now, everybody loves a puzzle.

12:45.097 --> 12:46.974
I get that.

12:47.057 --> 12:51.687
Everybody loves the secret word
that solves everything.

12:51.770 --> 12:54.190
But let's not call conspiracy

12:54.273 --> 12:56.275
something that could
just as easily be described

12:56.358 --> 12:57.985
as incompetence.

12:58.068 --> 13:00.988
Now, look, I have workers
come to my house every week.

13:01.071 --> 13:05.868
I mean, every damn week
to fix a broken faucet.

13:05.951 --> 13:08.537
They say they fixed it.
About a week goes by,

13:08.621 --> 13:11.415
I have to call somebody else
to fix their work.

13:11.499 --> 13:14.502
That's not a conspiracy.
That is incompetence.

13:14.585 --> 13:18.506
People do just enough work
to get by.

13:18.589 --> 13:21.091
So the camera was broken
outside of Epstein's cell.

13:21.175 --> 13:22.843
Incompetence.

13:22.927 --> 13:25.763
The guards were surfing the Web,
and then they fell asleep.

13:25.846 --> 13:27.389
Incompetence.

13:27.473 --> 13:30.017
The prison didn't secure
the crime scene.

13:30.100 --> 13:33.687
Incompetence.
I mean, that is America.

13:33.771 --> 13:35.731
Okay.

13:35.814 --> 13:40.069
All right, so we start
with suicide.

13:40.152 --> 13:41.445
I want to agree with Adrian.

13:41.529 --> 13:43.239
I'm not into
conspiracy theories,

13:43.322 --> 13:44.740
but, um...

13:44.823 --> 13:47.743
let's just look at 2006.

13:47.826 --> 13:52.706
Epstein got arrested
for abusing underage girls,

13:52.790 --> 13:54.208
and guess what happened.

13:54.291 --> 13:56.418
He was let off with

13:56.502 --> 13:59.588
a single count of prostitutio.

13:59.672 --> 14:03.801
The FBI found 34 victims
and could have found more,

14:03.884 --> 14:05.886
but they were shut down.

14:05.970 --> 14:09.056
We believe that
we proceeded appropriately.

14:09.139 --> 14:11.600
DIANE:
Epstein was supposed
to go to prison,

14:11.684 --> 14:14.061
but he got let out every day

14:14.144 --> 14:17.273
and raped more underage girls.

14:17.356 --> 14:20.401
And then, for eight years,
he was supposed to check in

14:20.484 --> 14:22.236
with the New York Police

14:22.319 --> 14:24.989
every 90 days because
he was a Level 3 sex offender.

14:25.072 --> 14:26.907
And you know how often
he checked in?

14:26.991 --> 14:29.243
Never.

14:29.326 --> 14:31.579
So, what are you saying?

14:31.662 --> 14:33.163
Well, we all
have to obey the law.

14:33.247 --> 14:35.457
I mean, if we're told that
we have to check in

14:35.541 --> 14:39.003
with the police every 90 days,
we do it.

14:39.086 --> 14:40.462
But certain people
don't have to.

14:40.546 --> 14:42.464
They're given special treatment.

14:42.548 --> 14:45.968
Epstein had friends
in high places,

14:46.051 --> 14:49.346
and then they stopped being
his friends, and they started

14:49.430 --> 14:51.015
worrying about him.

14:52.349 --> 14:53.851
And that's why he's dead.

14:53.934 --> 14:55.936
Well, I'm so glad
you don't believe in...

14:56.020 --> 14:57.271
conspiracy theories.

14:57.354 --> 14:58.314
That is America.

14:58.397 --> 15:01.817
That is not incompetence.

15:01.900 --> 15:06.030
It's a special fucking off-ramp
for the well-connected.

15:06.113 --> 15:07.781
Okay.

15:07.865 --> 15:09.700
All right, let's just...

15:09.783 --> 15:11.368
split into three groups:

15:11.452 --> 15:12.703
medical evidence,

15:12.786 --> 15:16.123
post-death facts,
pretrial facts.

15:16.206 --> 15:17.958
Facts.

15:20.794 --> 15:23.339
So... we were just upstairs

15:23.422 --> 15:25.966
for a synergy talk.

15:26.050 --> 15:28.010
Okay. What does that mean?

15:28.093 --> 15:30.137
We have to reduce
our payroll by 20%.

15:30.220 --> 15:32.222
-What? Wha...
-ADRIAN: Yep. 20.

15:32.306 --> 15:35.517
Payroll? What, as-as-as in
office space or...?

15:35.601 --> 15:37.645
No, no. Lawyers.

15:37.728 --> 15:39.688
So we've been putting
some initial thoughts together,

15:39.772 --> 15:41.565
seeing if there's anybody
we could agree on.

15:41.649 --> 15:44.068
Well, we can agree we're not
gonna lose 20% of our lawyers.

15:44.151 --> 15:45.653
We have a lot of paralegals.

15:45.736 --> 15:47.529
-What about Goldie?
-No. She's really bright

15:47.613 --> 15:49.198
and has excellent
research skills,

15:49.281 --> 15:52.034
and paralegals aren't gonna
get us there.

15:52.117 --> 15:54.411
-I for one could lose Kevin.
-Are you kidding?

15:54.495 --> 15:55.704
The-the associates
look up to him.

15:55.788 --> 15:57.206
We'd have a mutiny on our hands.

15:57.289 --> 15:58.457
-Uh, Lucy?
-No. No.

15:58.540 --> 16:00.709
-In fact, she deserves a raise.
-DIANE: This is gonna look like

16:00.793 --> 16:02.336
a disaster to our clients.

16:02.419 --> 16:03.754
Like the firm is going down

16:03.837 --> 16:05.547
and we're throwing
the ballast over.

16:05.631 --> 16:07.049
Yeah, I know.
(inhales deeply)

16:07.132 --> 16:09.760
So.... who do we let go?

16:13.931 --> 16:16.225
(indistinct chatter)

16:16.308 --> 16:17.601
JAY:
Have you heard from
any character witnesses yet?

16:17.685 --> 16:19.561
We talked to one
of his friends in prison.

16:19.645 --> 16:21.980
-Epstein had a friend in prison?
-Epstein told him
he took care of

16:22.064 --> 16:24.274
the most important thing on
the jet before he got arrested.

16:24.358 --> 16:26.193
-What was the most
important thing?
-No idea,

16:26.276 --> 16:28.570
but he was arrested getting off
of his private jet at Teterboro.

16:28.654 --> 16:30.030
That was the last time
he was free.

16:30.114 --> 16:31.740
So I was thinking
we should go through

16:31.824 --> 16:34.284
the police photos of the arrest,
see who else was on the jet.

16:34.368 --> 16:36.620
I guess he could have talked
to one of his staff members.

16:39.123 --> 16:40.249
(exhales sharply)

16:40.332 --> 16:42.251
What?

16:42.334 --> 16:43.460
I know him.

16:43.544 --> 16:45.921
Wha... Who is it?

16:46.004 --> 16:47.923
LUCCA:
Andreas.

16:48.006 --> 16:49.967
Hairdresser to the stars.

16:50.050 --> 16:52.928
How do you know
a hairdresser to the stars?

16:53.011 --> 16:54.930
Bianca?

16:58.976 --> 17:00.394
(elevator bell dings)

17:02.229 --> 17:05.065
STELLA:
So, Julius,
you're a federal employee.

17:05.149 --> 17:06.608
Is what you're
coming forward with

17:06.692 --> 17:08.444
based on a reasonable belief

17:08.527 --> 17:11.989
that there's been a violation
of the law, gross mismanagement

17:12.072 --> 17:13.615
or abuse of authority?

17:13.699 --> 17:16.118
So fraud, waste or abuse?

17:16.201 --> 17:17.578
Abuse of authority.

17:17.661 --> 17:18.954
STELLA:
I am all ears.

17:19.038 --> 17:20.748
What exactly
is he protected from?

17:20.831 --> 17:22.791
STELLA:
Anything that
constitutes retaliation.

17:22.875 --> 17:26.336
-5-USC-2302 makes it
a federal crime.
-And who enforces this?

17:26.420 --> 17:29.089
STELLA:
The Office of
the Inspector General.

17:29.173 --> 17:30.883
That would be me.

17:30.966 --> 17:32.760
JULIUS:
Okay.

17:32.843 --> 17:35.262
-STELLA: You ready?
-Yeah.

17:39.725 --> 17:43.771
JULIUS:
There is a document
titled Memo 618.

17:50.778 --> 17:52.404
What do you need?

17:53.405 --> 17:55.824
Hi. Is Andreas in?

17:55.908 --> 17:57.618
-What time is your appointment?
-Oh, uh,

17:57.701 --> 17:59.203
no, I don't...
I don't have an appointment.

17:59.286 --> 18:02.831
Ma'am, Andreas is booked
two months in advance.

18:02.915 --> 18:05.000
Uh, I can pencil
a consultation in

18:05.083 --> 18:07.461
for... September.

18:07.544 --> 18:10.172
Tell him it's Lucca Quinn
from Saint Lucia.

18:10.255 --> 18:13.383
Yeah, unfortunately,
Andreas is quite busy.

18:13.467 --> 18:14.885
Maybe another time.

18:15.928 --> 18:18.806
Tell him I'm... Bianca's friend.

18:24.436 --> 18:28.023
Yeah, there's a lady here
who said she's Bianca's friend.

18:28.106 --> 18:30.317
-Lucca Quinn.
-ANDREAS: Lucca!

18:30.400 --> 18:34.029
-Andreas, hi.
-(laughs) Hi.

18:34.112 --> 18:35.864
Uh, reschedule Mrs. Roth
for tomorrow.

18:35.948 --> 18:38.033
-Oh, she just had her hair wash.
-Well, then, blow-dry it

18:38.116 --> 18:39.785
-and tell her I'm busy.
-Oh, no, I don't need a cut.

18:39.868 --> 18:41.537
-I just have a-a question.
-Come back, come back.

18:41.620 --> 18:42.996
Sorry.
I-I didn't know who you were.

18:43.997 --> 18:45.541
She's new. I'm firing her.

18:45.624 --> 18:48.168
-Oh, no, not for me.
-No, not because of you.

18:48.252 --> 18:50.045
'Cause she's useless.
Get out of the chair.

18:50.128 --> 18:51.713
Go ahead. Go. Go.

18:51.797 --> 18:53.131
Thank you.

18:53.215 --> 18:55.050
-Sit.
-(Lucca clears throat)

18:55.134 --> 18:56.677
How long? Three weeks?

18:56.760 --> 18:58.679
Uh, yeah, but I'm thinking
of growing it out.

18:58.762 --> 19:00.472
I see some damage here.

19:00.556 --> 19:01.765
(sniffs)

19:01.849 --> 19:03.392
Adona shampoo?

19:03.475 --> 19:05.602
-Janguree conditioner?
-Yes.

19:05.686 --> 19:08.814
You might as well pour concrete
on your hair.

19:10.649 --> 19:12.568
These. Use these.

19:12.651 --> 19:14.027
Thank you.

19:14.111 --> 19:16.029
Uh, but I'm here
about one of your clients.

19:16.113 --> 19:17.906
Oh, Bianca hasn't been in
in a week.

19:17.990 --> 19:20.742
Oh, no. Um, Jeffrey Epstein?

19:22.786 --> 19:24.413
Get out of here.

19:28.166 --> 19:31.587
He is unequivocally
not an official client.

19:31.670 --> 19:33.922
I only cut his hair
as a favor to Ghislaine.

19:34.006 --> 19:35.966
I don't want to get caught up
in any of his mess.

19:36.049 --> 19:37.718
Yeah, but you were
on a flight with him

19:37.801 --> 19:40.679
-right before his arrest.
-It was a midflight haircut.

19:40.762 --> 19:43.265
He knew he was being arrested.
He wanted to look good.

19:43.348 --> 19:46.518
Plus, prison haircuts
are just brutal.

19:48.520 --> 19:50.314
Who else was on the flight?

19:50.397 --> 19:51.940
(whispering): I shouldn't be
talking about this.

19:52.024 --> 19:53.567
-It's not safe.
-Okay.

19:53.650 --> 19:56.945
On the plane, did Epstein
seem nervous? Worried?

19:57.029 --> 19:58.697
No, no, I was the one
that was nervous.

19:58.780 --> 20:00.532
-Why?
-Because...

20:03.035 --> 20:04.286
-Nothing.
-Andreas, what?

20:04.369 --> 20:05.537
Nothing.

20:05.621 --> 20:07.623
You are lying,
and you're terrible at it.

20:07.706 --> 20:09.750
Just lean in toward me
and whisper.

20:09.833 --> 20:11.335
(whispers):
I can't.

20:11.418 --> 20:13.795
I'll tell you a secret
if you tell me yours.

20:16.214 --> 20:17.966
What secret?

20:18.050 --> 20:19.426
No, you first.

20:26.224 --> 20:28.810
(whispers):
He gave me an envelope.

20:28.894 --> 20:31.396
Epstein did? Why?

20:31.480 --> 20:34.149
No, y-your turn.

20:34.232 --> 20:37.152
I played poker with four
of the most powerful women

20:37.235 --> 20:38.862
-in the world.
-Fuck you. You did not.

20:38.946 --> 20:41.490
Bianca and who else?

20:41.573 --> 20:43.450
Why would he give you
an envelope?

20:43.533 --> 20:44.701
-Beyoncé?
-No.

20:44.785 --> 20:46.161
It better not be
some political woman,

20:46.244 --> 20:48.163
-someone I don't know.
-You'll know all of them.

20:48.246 --> 20:50.165
Andreas, tell me.

20:50.249 --> 20:51.625
He...

20:51.708 --> 20:53.835
He knew Ghislaine
was a friend of mine

20:53.919 --> 20:56.838
and that she'd be in
in a couple of weeks

20:56.922 --> 20:59.383
to pick it up-- the envelope.
But she never showed.

20:59.466 --> 21:01.051
I think she's in hiding.

21:01.134 --> 21:02.761
(whispers):
Or dead.

21:04.763 --> 21:07.057
So, you still have it?

21:09.142 --> 21:10.811
Can I see it?

21:23.740 --> 21:24.908
You never opened it?

21:24.992 --> 21:27.035
No.

21:28.161 --> 21:30.163
Maybe I should hold on to it.

21:40.674 --> 21:44.094
This video is to establish
chain of custody for an envelope

21:44.177 --> 21:46.179
reportedly given
by Jeffrey Epstein

21:46.263 --> 21:50.517
to his employee and girlfriend,
Ghislaine Maxwell.

21:50.600 --> 21:54.021
It is Thursday, May 21, 2020,

21:54.104 --> 21:57.232
and we have been given
permission by Wilbur Dincon,

21:57.315 --> 21:59.860
U.S. attorney for the
Southern District of New York,

21:59.943 --> 22:03.405
to open this envelope and record
its contents in accordance

22:03.488 --> 22:05.574
with our mission
as investigators

22:05.657 --> 22:07.743
of Mr. Epstein's death.
Go ahead.

22:11.997 --> 22:14.416
All right,
the envelope is now open.

22:14.499 --> 22:16.293
And, uh...

22:17.669 --> 22:20.297
There appears to be
a key inside.

22:23.341 --> 22:25.761
No apparent markings.

22:25.844 --> 22:27.262
And, uh...

22:27.346 --> 22:30.766
there's a ten-digit number
on the other side.

22:30.849 --> 22:32.142
(paper rustling)

22:32.225 --> 22:34.061
Okay.

22:35.103 --> 22:36.146
All right.

22:36.229 --> 22:37.773
There appears to be

22:37.856 --> 22:42.069
an eight-and-a-half-by-11
letter folded in thirds.

22:42.152 --> 22:44.738
Nothing on the outside
of the letter.

22:44.821 --> 22:47.282
We will now open the letter.

22:47.365 --> 22:49.117
And....

22:49.201 --> 22:51.536
there is handwriting
on the inside,

22:51.620 --> 22:53.121
which reads...

22:53.205 --> 22:54.956
"If I'm dead,

22:55.040 --> 22:56.750
watch out for Bud."

22:56.833 --> 22:59.252
Whoa, who's Bud?

22:59.336 --> 23:02.047
-The killer?
-LIZ: We are now

23:02.130 --> 23:03.799
comparing the handwriting

23:03.882 --> 23:08.136
to the last note
Mr. Epstein wrote in his cell,

23:08.220 --> 23:12.349
and they appear to be written
by the same hand.

23:15.894 --> 23:17.187
Wait, what's that?

23:17.270 --> 23:18.355
MARISSA:
What is that?

23:20.941 --> 23:22.526
What is that?

23:25.237 --> 23:26.571
LUCCA:
Is it a code?

23:26.655 --> 23:28.115
"Lady M.S."

23:28.198 --> 23:29.282
Or a-a bank account?

23:29.366 --> 23:30.784
LIZ:
Maybe.

23:30.867 --> 23:34.204
And who is Lady M.S.?

23:34.287 --> 23:36.123
A pet name for Ghislaine, maybe?

23:38.416 --> 23:40.335
-(indistinct chatter)
-LIZ: We have a new lead.

23:40.418 --> 23:42.337
"Bud."

23:42.420 --> 23:45.173
Is it someone
who had it out for Epstein?

23:45.257 --> 23:46.466
Why would he fear him?

23:46.550 --> 23:48.677
Uh, let's see,
I'll take, uh, Mike,

23:48.760 --> 23:51.471
John, Damian and Linda
to pursue that lead.

23:51.555 --> 23:53.473
All right, who wants
to check these numbers?

23:53.557 --> 23:57.144
This could be a bank account.
Cayman Islands? Uh, a safe?

23:57.227 --> 23:58.687
We can take that.
Epstein was always trying

23:58.770 --> 24:00.021
to hide money from his victims.

24:00.105 --> 24:02.482
Plus, those underage girls
are still trying

24:02.566 --> 24:04.901
to recover damages,
so a hidden account means

24:04.985 --> 24:07.863
-more to recover.
-Good, and last, the key.

24:07.946 --> 24:10.740
-What does it open?
-Uh, Marissa and I have the key.

24:10.824 --> 24:12.659
LIZ:
Okay, good. Good, good, good.

24:12.742 --> 24:14.369
All right, let's get moving.
We'll get back

24:14.452 --> 24:15.537
-together this afternoon.
-Hey, Liz?

24:15.620 --> 24:16.788
-Hey, we need to...
-Okay, all right.

24:16.872 --> 24:18.165
Anything you can find.

24:18.248 --> 24:20.000
Bud-- dead or alive.

24:20.083 --> 24:22.210
JAY:
This is a manufacturer's stamp.

24:22.294 --> 24:24.880
-We should be able to track down
where it was made.
-Good.

24:24.963 --> 24:26.089
Did you hear?

24:26.173 --> 24:27.174
What?

24:27.257 --> 24:29.384
We are all going to be fired.

24:29.467 --> 24:31.678
-What?
-KEVIN: They're laying off 40%.

24:31.761 --> 24:33.221
Just paralegals, right?

24:33.305 --> 24:35.557
-No, us.
-What about investigators?

24:35.640 --> 24:38.393
Fuck you. It all comes down
to you, doesn't it?

24:38.476 --> 24:41.188
-Oh, my God!
-That's what they're
in there talking about.

24:41.271 --> 24:43.732
Who to fire.

24:43.815 --> 24:45.942
Rosalyn has the fewest
billable hours.

24:46.026 --> 24:47.861
Oh, because she had
an appendectomy.

24:47.944 --> 24:50.238
We don't fire people
because they're sick.

24:50.322 --> 24:52.949
DIANE:
Felicia-- she's
the newest associate.

24:53.033 --> 24:55.744
-And the smartest.
-Mm.

24:55.827 --> 24:57.245
Adrian?

24:58.496 --> 25:01.166
J-Just...

25:01.249 --> 25:05.086
You know, we do have
two investigators.

25:15.722 --> 25:17.432
What if we refuse to do this?

25:17.515 --> 25:19.100
DIANE:
And get dismissed by our firm?

25:19.184 --> 25:20.227
No.

25:20.310 --> 25:22.270
What if we buy ourselves out?

25:22.354 --> 25:24.940
♪ ♪

25:25.023 --> 25:27.442
Our merger agreement stipulates
that partnership rights revert

25:27.525 --> 25:30.612
if we exercise our option
within the first year

25:30.695 --> 25:33.323
to refund the purchase.

25:33.406 --> 25:34.658
How much?

25:34.741 --> 25:36.326
20 million.

25:38.203 --> 25:39.829
That's a lot.

25:39.913 --> 25:41.665
We've had a good year, Diane.

25:41.748 --> 25:43.583
Not a $20 million year.

25:43.667 --> 25:46.127
You know, Dincon implied
more work could come our way

25:46.211 --> 25:48.296
if we come through
with this Epstein review.

25:48.380 --> 25:50.340
And if we get a bank loan
for the rest...

25:50.423 --> 25:51.841
Our bank won't do that.

25:51.925 --> 25:54.094
I make a few promises,
they might.

25:54.177 --> 25:56.763
-Promise of future profits?
-Maybe. Let me...

25:56.846 --> 25:58.139
make a few calls.

25:58.223 --> 26:01.476
We have got to get
out of this now.

26:01.559 --> 26:03.770
We let them downsize us,
we all know...

26:03.853 --> 26:05.814
-it's just the beginning.
-LIZ: Okay.

26:05.897 --> 26:08.566
Just let-let's not make
any promises that we can't keep.

26:10.735 --> 26:12.487
I just had this...

26:12.570 --> 26:14.906
really odd moment of déjà vu.

26:14.990 --> 26:17.158
Being married...

26:17.242 --> 26:19.119
we had the exact same
conversation.

26:20.578 --> 26:22.122
How'd that work out?

26:22.205 --> 26:23.915
We made promises
we couldn't keep.

26:23.999 --> 26:25.166
(laughs)

26:25.250 --> 26:26.793
Yep.

26:28.878 --> 26:30.547
Yeah, this is one of mine.

26:30.630 --> 26:32.465
My manufacturer stamp's
right there.

26:32.549 --> 26:34.050
Can you tell us who ordered it?

26:34.134 --> 26:37.887
(chuckles) The cheap fucker
died owing me $190.

26:37.971 --> 26:40.015
Add that to his rap sheet.

26:40.098 --> 26:41.641
-Epstein?
-I'm not saying,

26:41.725 --> 26:43.184
but... yeah.

26:43.268 --> 26:46.021
Is there any way to match
a key to a property

26:46.104 --> 26:48.023
-or a locker or anything?
-No.

26:48.106 --> 26:50.817
But even if there was,
I couldn't tell you anything.

26:52.152 --> 26:53.570
What if we paid his bill?

26:58.116 --> 27:00.452
Okay, uh, $190.

27:00.535 --> 27:02.412
With tax, 202.

27:03.621 --> 27:04.998
I only have 45.

27:05.081 --> 27:06.583
JAY:
Oh, okay.

27:06.666 --> 27:09.878
Uh, what's this key to?

27:09.961 --> 27:11.629
Mm, in the hand first.

27:15.633 --> 27:16.718
What is it to?

27:16.801 --> 27:18.678
No idea.

27:18.762 --> 27:20.430
-Oh, come on!
-We probably cut

27:20.513 --> 27:22.724
300 of these for his homes
all over the world.

27:22.807 --> 27:24.726
-Thanks for nothing.
-Talk to his architect.

27:24.809 --> 27:26.311
She's the one
who wanted them cut.

27:26.394 --> 27:27.896
She probably knows more.

27:27.979 --> 27:30.482
LIZ:
"If I'm dead,
watch out for Bud."

27:30.565 --> 27:31.858
Who is Bud?

27:31.941 --> 27:33.068
What have we found?

27:33.151 --> 27:34.736
Nothing-- no known associates,

27:34.819 --> 27:36.905
-no family, no friends.
-LEAH: And no one from prison.

27:36.988 --> 27:39.407
Well, have you checked
Prince Andrew's people?

27:39.491 --> 27:41.242
ROSALYN:
And anyone connected
to Ghislaine.

27:41.326 --> 27:43.328
DIANE:
What if, instead of a name,

27:43.411 --> 27:45.580
it's... it's initials?

27:45.663 --> 27:48.249
I mean, "Bud," it's all in caps.

27:48.333 --> 27:50.585
Well, if it's B.U.D.,
then we should be

27:50.668 --> 27:52.253
looking at last names
beginning with "D"

27:52.337 --> 27:54.214
in Epstein's little black book.

27:54.297 --> 27:56.049
"Dafoe"-- I found a lawyer,

27:56.132 --> 27:57.592
Benjamin Dafoe,

27:57.675 --> 27:59.886
but there's no
middle name listed.

27:59.969 --> 28:02.138
ROSALYN:
Got him-- his Wikipedia page.

28:02.222 --> 28:03.765
"Benjamin Ulrich Dafoe."

28:03.848 --> 28:05.183
Oh.

28:05.266 --> 28:06.935
I'll call him.

28:07.018 --> 28:09.396
WOMAN:
Are you sure this is

28:09.479 --> 28:11.731
an official investigation?
Because I've been dealing with

28:11.815 --> 28:14.234
a lot of lookie-loos
who want an Epstein souvenir.

28:14.317 --> 28:16.444
-No, I...
-Or worse, they come in

28:16.528 --> 28:17.654
pretending they want
a consultation

28:17.737 --> 28:19.280
just so they can yell at me,

28:19.364 --> 28:21.366
"How could you enable
that predator?!"

28:21.449 --> 28:23.660
Did Epstein ever mention
anyone named Bud?

28:23.743 --> 28:25.578
Someone he might have
been afraid of?

28:25.662 --> 28:27.789
