40:36.725 --> 40:38.644
How do you know about that?

40:38.727 --> 40:40.563
What?

40:40.646 --> 40:42.690
Bud.

40:42.773 --> 40:44.984
Well, that was
the weirdest thing.

40:45.067 --> 40:46.777
That... that
really stayed with me.

40:46.861 --> 40:47.903
What?

40:49.822 --> 40:52.199
Well, Trump leaned into Jeffee--

40:52.283 --> 40:54.118
oh, I had to call him "Jeffee"--

40:54.201 --> 40:56.370
and, uh, he whispered,

40:56.453 --> 40:58.372
"How's Bud?"
And then Jeffee whispered back,

40:58.455 --> 40:59.790
"No problems."

40:59.874 --> 41:01.375
And that was it.

41:03.127 --> 41:05.379
And why was that weird?

41:05.462 --> 41:07.715
Well, because they both got
really serious.

41:07.798 --> 41:10.926
Like they...
like they had to be careful.

41:11.010 --> 41:13.053
Like they were worried.

41:18.767 --> 41:20.686
WOMAN:
Did he have a dog? Maybe they
were talking about his dog.

41:20.769 --> 41:23.022
All we know is that
Trump somehow knew Bud,

41:23.105 --> 41:24.899
or maybe still does, but we
still don't know who Bud is.

41:24.982 --> 41:26.984
I just heard back on 4chan.

41:27.067 --> 41:29.403
-MARISSA: What?
What did they say?
-Why are we on 4chan?

41:29.486 --> 41:31.071
Epstein's death
was first reported,

41:31.155 --> 41:32.698
even before
the mainstream media,

41:32.781 --> 41:34.074
by a poster on 4chan,

41:34.158 --> 41:36.493
someone with insider knowledge.

41:36.577 --> 41:38.579
-Is that true?
-Yuh-huh.
And I just wrote to him,

41:38.662 --> 41:41.916
asking if Bill Barr is involved,
and why was 12 hours a deadline?

41:41.999 --> 41:43.918
Okay, okay.
What are we talking about here?

41:44.001 --> 41:45.920
We-we think we may have
deciphered a message.

41:46.003 --> 41:48.088
-I'll-I'll tell you later.
-"Barr picked up Epstein's body

41:48.172 --> 41:49.423
"within 12 hours.

41:49.506 --> 41:51.800
It was taken
to the Virgin Islands."

41:51.884 --> 41:53.260
-The fuck?
-That's why the code read:

41:53.344 --> 41:54.970
"Call Bill.
He'll have 12 hours."

41:55.054 --> 41:57.431
Wait a second, wait a second.
What-what-what's going on?

41:57.514 --> 41:59.642
NBC News reported
that a mysterious associate

41:59.725 --> 42:02.269
picked up Epstein's body
from the medical examiner.

42:02.353 --> 42:03.437
He wouldn't give his name,

42:03.520 --> 42:05.439
and he's never been identified.

42:05.522 --> 42:08.275
And you think the attorney
general of the United States

42:08.359 --> 42:10.444
is that person?

42:10.527 --> 42:12.279
-It makes as much sense
as anything else.
-(computer chimes)

42:12.363 --> 42:14.114
-No, it doesn't.
-Wait, I just wrote
to him, asking,

42:14.198 --> 42:16.408
"I thought Epstein
was buried in Florida,"

42:16.492 --> 42:18.661
and he just wrote back...

42:21.830 --> 42:25.459
"Check the tomb. It's empty."

42:25.542 --> 42:27.920
Oh, come...
What is going on here?

42:28.003 --> 42:30.631
This... N-No. This is crazy.

42:30.714 --> 42:33.676
All these theories are built
on a hairdresser's envelope.

42:33.759 --> 42:36.637
If it's a prank,
then all of this is bullshit.

42:36.720 --> 42:40.474
-The government charges
Julius Cain...
-Judge Cain.

42:40.557 --> 42:44.561
...Julius Cain with violating
Chapter 18, USC 201,

42:44.645 --> 42:47.690
a Chapter 4 felony, punishable
by up to 15 years imprisonment.

42:47.773 --> 42:49.942
We allege he accepted bribes
from a plaintiff

42:50.025 --> 42:52.486
-in an eminent domain case.
-DIANE: Your Honor,

42:52.569 --> 42:54.280
Judge Cain pleads not guilty

42:54.363 --> 42:57.324
and should be released on bail
to await trial.

42:57.408 --> 42:59.285
He has extensive ties
to the community

42:59.368 --> 43:01.495
and is not a flight risk.

43:01.578 --> 43:03.747
(gavel slams)

43:05.207 --> 43:06.875
This is retribution?

43:06.959 --> 43:10.337
-For whistleblowing?
-That's my guess.

43:10.421 --> 43:13.173
We left the inspector general,
and the next day I get arrested.

43:13.257 --> 43:16.302
How could they know?
How could... How do they know?

43:17.553 --> 43:20.681
So maybe it's her clerk.

43:20.764 --> 43:22.599
Or...

43:23.600 --> 43:24.977
Or...?

43:27.605 --> 43:30.566
The inspector general.

43:30.649 --> 43:32.026
(scoffs)

43:32.109 --> 43:35.321
If that's so, what do I do?

43:36.780 --> 43:38.449
Fight.

43:45.039 --> 43:46.540
That was fast.

43:46.623 --> 43:48.625
So, who are you cutting?

43:50.085 --> 43:51.879
Everyone made
a good-faith effort

43:51.962 --> 43:55.549
to reduce the staff, Gavin,
but in the end, the...

43:55.632 --> 43:57.885
the arrangement
didn't work for us.

43:57.968 --> 43:59.511
No hard feelings.

43:59.595 --> 44:02.348
I don't understand.

44:02.431 --> 44:05.893
Uh, we are prepared to buy
our way out of the partnership,

44:05.976 --> 44:08.270
as enumerated in the contract.

44:08.354 --> 44:11.732
Ah, yes, well,
that is certainly your right.

44:11.815 --> 44:13.567
-Within the first year.
-ADRIAN: Good.

44:13.650 --> 44:17.321
And we're ready. We have
the 20 million required.

44:18.322 --> 44:19.782
You mean 80 million.

44:20.991 --> 44:22.910
No, 20 million.

44:22.993 --> 44:26.288
We all signed a merger agreement
that stresses "20 million."

44:26.372 --> 44:28.040
Uh, no.

44:28.123 --> 44:32.211
The contract says 20, provided,
according to clause 46-B,

44:32.294 --> 44:34.213
that all Reddick/Boseman
name partners

44:34.296 --> 44:36.090
earn more in revenue
after the merger

44:36.173 --> 44:38.258
than they did the year prior.

44:38.342 --> 44:39.760
Which we did.

44:39.843 --> 44:42.721
-No, you didn't.
-Oh, my God.

44:42.805 --> 44:44.306
What?

44:45.808 --> 44:48.560
That's why you gave it to me.

44:48.644 --> 44:51.772
It wasn't a gift.
It was a curse.

44:51.855 --> 44:54.108
Fuck.

44:54.191 --> 44:56.068
-Pro bono.
-DIANE: He gave me
pro bono cases

44:56.151 --> 44:58.654
to keep my billable hours low.

44:58.737 --> 45:01.281
Well, I-I also knew
that you'd be good at it, too.

45:01.365 --> 45:02.783
You fucker.

45:02.866 --> 45:03.951
(scoffs)
Diane. Name-calling?

45:04.034 --> 45:05.786
We're all on the same side here.

45:05.869 --> 45:08.622
You set me up,
just to keep us from leaving.

45:10.541 --> 45:12.960
I'm a jealous boss.

45:13.043 --> 45:14.795
I don't want you to leave.

45:14.878 --> 45:18.298
I want to cling close to you,
like a vine.

45:18.382 --> 45:20.259
Also, I kind of like
the look on your face

45:20.342 --> 45:21.510
that you were outplayed.

45:23.053 --> 45:24.972
The Zen master said

45:25.055 --> 45:27.307
that "in every experience
there is a lesson."

45:27.391 --> 45:32.104
And the lesson here
is that you three are fucked.

45:41.530 --> 45:44.283
Can... can you call the bank?

45:44.366 --> 45:46.368
Yes.

45:48.745 --> 45:50.205
Liz.

45:54.334 --> 45:56.670
Shit.

45:56.753 --> 45:58.881
As you can see, the amount
of suspicious activity

45:58.964 --> 46:01.467
surrounding Epstein's death
is... it's extraordinary.

46:01.550 --> 46:04.178
The number of things
that went wrong in the prison...

46:04.261 --> 46:06.430
The number of people
that wanted him dead?

46:06.513 --> 46:08.140
And the note he left
Ghislaine Maxwell,

46:08.223 --> 46:09.641
uh, "Watch out for Bud."

46:09.725 --> 46:11.852
Mm, the note he left
with the hairdresser?

46:11.935 --> 46:14.188
Uh, a celebrity hairstylist.

46:14.271 --> 46:15.689
ROSALYN:
He was also a part

46:15.772 --> 46:17.524
of a global pedophile ring
that was supported

46:17.608 --> 46:19.193
by intelligence services.

46:19.276 --> 46:21.403
Well...

46:21.487 --> 46:23.530
this is very extensive work.

46:23.614 --> 46:24.865
We're nowhere near done.

46:24.948 --> 46:26.825
We'll need at least
a few more weeks.

46:26.909 --> 46:28.494
LIZ:
We have a team down
in the Virgin Islands

46:28.577 --> 46:30.579
checking out Epstein's island.

46:36.502 --> 46:39.087
And we have a key
that we need to check.

46:39.171 --> 46:41.089
And what is this?

46:41.173 --> 46:43.717
Oh, uh, this is a-a code

46:43.800 --> 46:46.887
that reads: "Call Bill.
He will have 12 hours."

46:46.970 --> 46:49.556
Hmm. And what is that from?

46:49.640 --> 46:52.267
LUCCA:
It's from a book
Epstein referenced.

46:52.351 --> 46:54.102
It's a novel written
by Bill Barr's father.

46:54.186 --> 46:58.065
It's about space
and-and-and some sex slaves.

46:59.107 --> 47:00.192
And people...

47:00.275 --> 47:01.860
All right, so...

47:01.944 --> 47:03.612
where are we left?

47:03.695 --> 47:05.447
Uh, well, you-you said
you wanted us

47:05.531 --> 47:07.699
-to think outside the box.
-And...?

47:07.783 --> 47:11.203
And, um, well, uh,
Epstein had odd interests,

47:11.286 --> 47:14.581
and he seemed
to want to live forever.

47:14.665 --> 47:18.377
Uh, uh, we're not sure if Bud
is someone he feared

47:18.460 --> 47:20.754
or-or-or something he lost.

47:20.837 --> 47:23.924
Bud seems to be just one piece

47:24.007 --> 47:26.093
of the puzzle
we can't figure out.

47:26.176 --> 47:28.554
Okay.

47:28.637 --> 47:30.806
Why don't we take a pause?

47:32.015 --> 47:33.767
-A pause?
-Yeah.

47:33.850 --> 47:37.479
I think we've gotten
a little lost in the weeds here.

47:37.563 --> 47:42.442
You've done some great work,
but once we get into...

47:42.526 --> 47:45.112
this kind of conjecture,
I can't use it.

47:45.195 --> 47:46.613
I'm sorry.

47:46.697 --> 47:49.825
We will send someone
to pick up your notes

47:49.908 --> 47:53.245
and work product,
along with the materials

47:53.328 --> 47:56.790
left for Ms. Maxwell,
including the key.

47:56.873 --> 47:59.126
We'll have to get that to you.

47:59.209 --> 48:01.587
Fine.

48:01.670 --> 48:03.422
DIANE:
Mr. Dincon?

48:03.505 --> 48:05.340
Hmm?

48:05.424 --> 48:08.176
What is Memo 618?

48:09.219 --> 48:10.637
Why do you ask?

48:10.721 --> 48:13.390
Jeffrey Epstein's life
was built on it.

48:14.391 --> 48:16.518
Then you have your answer.

48:19.605 --> 48:21.648
(seabirds chirping)

48:28.572 --> 48:31.158
LIZ:
You should come home.
The investigation's over.

48:31.241 --> 48:33.243
DOJ is shutting us down.

48:33.327 --> 48:34.828
MARISSA:
But why would they do that?

48:34.911 --> 48:37.122
-We're so close.
-Yeah, well, in hindsight,

48:37.205 --> 48:40.000
I-I think we shouldn't have
let ourselves get carried away.

48:40.083 --> 48:42.669
I mean, what we found might have
been an interesting story,

48:42.753 --> 48:45.088
but it-it doesn't mean
that it was the truth.

48:45.172 --> 48:47.507
-Okay, we'll head back.
-Good.

48:47.591 --> 48:49.593
And bring the key.

48:51.553 --> 48:53.013
MARISSA:
Well, as long as we're here,

48:53.096 --> 48:55.265
we might as well
go ahead with it.

48:55.349 --> 48:57.184
JAY:
Good with me.

49:00.771 --> 49:03.482
MARISSA:
Wow.

49:03.565 --> 49:07.027
Not a lot of room for sex
or sacrifices in here.

49:07.110 --> 49:08.528
(Jay chuckles)

49:08.612 --> 49:10.739
He never threw anything away.

49:10.822 --> 49:14.534
This is what happens
when you die.

49:14.618 --> 49:18.330
You leave everything
for your relatives to clean up.

49:18.413 --> 49:21.708
"Welcome back, Mr. Epstein,
from 34 students

49:21.792 --> 49:26.004
in period-three science class,
the Dalton School."

49:26.088 --> 49:28.715
"Don't lose the fur coat."

49:30.676 --> 49:33.220
So, this is the room
on the blueprint,

49:33.303 --> 49:34.888
the one that read "Bud"?

49:34.971 --> 49:37.724
-Yeah.
-So, where's Bud?

49:37.808 --> 49:40.894
Bud could be anything.
One of the statues.

49:40.977 --> 49:42.688
One of the packages.

49:42.771 --> 49:45.065
Whatever this thing is in here.

49:45.148 --> 49:48.026
We're never gonna get
through all this.

49:55.617 --> 49:57.035
Uh, give me the key.

49:58.161 --> 49:59.287
What?

49:59.371 --> 50:00.664
Look.

50:01.498 --> 50:04.000
(gasps) Oh, my God.

50:04.084 --> 50:07.629
We're solving this.
We are solving this, you and I.

50:08.839 --> 50:11.216
-(exhales)
-Wait, wait, wait.

50:11.299 --> 50:13.802
What do you think
is on the other side?

50:13.885 --> 50:16.888
-Bud.
-Or Epstein.

50:16.972 --> 50:19.641
Bill Barr brought him down here,
and he's alive and hidden,

50:19.725 --> 50:22.018
-like in Parasite.
-Never saw it.

50:22.102 --> 50:25.105
What? How have you not seen it?

50:25.188 --> 50:27.941
-It won the Oscar.
It was a historic win...
-Do you want to open it?

50:28.024 --> 50:29.276
Okay. Yeah.

50:48.545 --> 50:49.755
Okay.

50:52.174 --> 50:54.050
That's how all mysteries end,
don't they?

50:54.134 --> 50:56.970
Empty, pointless, stupid.

50:57.053 --> 51:00.474
We were the stupid ones
for obsessing on "Bud."

51:00.557 --> 51:02.142
It probably had nothing
to do with him.

51:02.225 --> 51:06.146
Just a nickname
for something or someone.

51:06.229 --> 51:07.606
Yeah.

51:07.689 --> 51:10.859
I think we lost track
of the real story.

51:10.942 --> 51:12.736
Mm.

51:12.819 --> 51:15.322
The underage girls.

51:15.405 --> 51:18.992
We were chasing a whodunit
in the middle of a tragedy.

51:24.122 --> 51:26.041
We better go.

51:26.124 --> 51:28.794
-Motorboat is back
in ten minutes.
-Okay.

51:31.213 --> 51:33.465
(sighs)
Bye, Mr. Epstein.

51:33.548 --> 51:34.758
(gong clangs)

51:37.135 --> 51:39.179
Have fun in hell.

